I think a total ban on food delivery apps needs to happen. They make everyone more asocial and isolated, promote obesity and bad nutrition practices, they parody real cuisine, serve as reason to import more migrants for cheap slave labor, and actively make most restaurants worse.

It obviously kills real restaurants and bistros where you're meant to sit for hours and talk with friends, it makes people spend less time outdoors, it gives useless jobs to the worst types of migrants. I don't know why normies even use them but all food delivery apps need to go.

Food delivery apps make the world worse in every conceivable way. No one even enjoys the food more than a cheaper frozen meal. New restaurants are built with less tables because they'll market towards food delivery instead of real clients, soon no one will actually go out to eat.

Was having a beer (Stella Artois draft ofc.) with my buddy at our favorite outdoor bar and saw the pigeon without legs. Not sure if I have mentioned him here but there was a pigeon with both of his legs missing who was sort of a regular hanging around there every day last autumn.

It made me sad seeing him and thinking how he'll surely die in the cold but somehow he has made it through the winter and is doing well. Shows the extent of his willpower. Must have been through Berserk tier misfortunes in the snow and still made it. Lesson in here for hustlers.

Me and a friend went to a new "sushi restaurant" that opened in my town a few weeks ago and there was half a table inside, two seats. Alibaba tier interior. Obviously meant only for online food delivery app orders. Not a place where you can hang out for a few hours just drinking.

Well me and him can hang out drinking beer in literal junkyards but it's actually crazy how hostile to life places like this are. They want everyone sitting home eating stale Glovoslop in front of their laptops instead of having fun around town. Total food delivery app bans soon.

It's also obvious that no self-respecting real chef would work at a place like that with zero actual restaurant *guests* and the "sushi" will be indistinguishable from the frozen supermarket prepackaged ones. Diabolical. The only way food should leave restaurants is as leftovers.
